            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "nvim_notify may not have been the best thought out features . For context, I wanted to be able to forward some messages as system notifications rather than via vim's `:messages` system due to its interruptive nature. A proper fix would be a rework of messages but that seemed unlikely. Until this happens we have with vim.notify a behavior easily overridable  that may be later aliased to `nvim_echo( msg,  { notify: true}`.",
